&lt;hr>
&lt;h3 id="20250924">2025.09.24&lt;/h3>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>&amp;hellip;
续上篇&lt;/p>
&lt;p>For decades, 10,000 steps was &lt;strong style="color: red">touted&lt;/strong> as the magic number for good health.&lt;br>
几十年来，1万步被吹捧为良好健康的神奇数字。&lt;/p>
&lt;p>But the recommendation is more &lt;strong style="color: red">myth&lt;/strong> than science, and researchers have &lt;strong style="color: red">debunked&lt;/strong> it in recent years.&lt;br>
但这个建议更多地是未经证实的说法而非科学，而且研究者们在最近几年已经对此辟谣。&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>How Many Steps Do You Really Need in a Day? (1)</title><link>https://wanghaoyang1995.github.io/posts/english_learning/20250922-728761-1/</link><pubDate>Mon, 22 Sep 2025 20:52:52 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wanghaoyang1995.github.io/posts/english_learning/20250922-728761-1/</guid><description>&lt;p>原文链接: 


