&lt;/audio>
&lt;hr>
&lt;h3 id="20250922">2025.09.22&lt;/h3>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;h3 id="how-many-steps-do-you-really-need-in-a-day">How Many Steps Do You Really Need in a Day?&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Walking 10,000 steps a day has long been a fitness &lt;strong style="color: red">cliche&lt;/strong>.&lt;br>
每天走1万步已经成为老生常谈的健身法则。&lt;/p>
&lt;p>But new research suggests that the health benefits of walking &lt;strong style="color: red">ramp up&lt;/strong> until about 7,000 steps - before &lt;strong style="color: red">leveling out&lt;/strong>.&lt;br>
但是最新研究表明，步行的健康益处持续增加直到大约7000步达到峰值。&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Want higher pay? Don't change jobs (3)</title><link>https://wanghaoyang1995.github.io/posts/english_learning/20250918-726201-3/</link><pubDate>Thu, 18 Sep 2025 19:24:51 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wanghaoyang1995.github.io/posts/english_learning/20250918-726201-3/</guid><description>&lt;p>原文链接: 


